                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-284-off1517 t18230910-284-crimeloc1520"></join>. On the 6th of September, between three or four o'clock in the afternoon, the prisoner came to the shop, to match a pattern of blue printed cotton - I said we had none, and as she went out, I saw a piece of printed cotton under her arm, which had laid on a pile inside the door. I followed her into another shop, and as she came out, I asked her for the print that was under her arm - she said,</p>
